Mark dev w/ v1.x since I'm likely going to break semver

This is purely for clearer naming.

Signed-off-by: Brian Harring <ferringb@gmail.com>

Remove dead dcbuffer types

Signed-off-by: Brian Harring <ferringb@gmail.com>

Simplify multipass logic while maintaining the same byte output.

Comments were added to clarify, but multipass has a behaviour where it
inverts what's being hashed, using that to try and minimize hash collisions.

The utility of that logic should be revisited, but in the meantime, the two
branches of code are effectively the same sans the hash functions, thus unify
it down to one common codepath.

Signed-off-by: Brian Harring <ferringb@gmail.com>

cseek: reset avail_in/out for cfh->xzs (bug 708736)

Reset avail_in/out for cfh->xzs in order to correct interaction
with the crefill function. This solves a seek error for tarsync
as reported in bug 708736.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/708736
Signed-off-by: Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org>
Signed-off-by: Brian Harring <ferringb@gmail.com>
Formatting cleanup for recent changes
Remove redundant EDCB_SRC_ID intermediate ref_id variables
Refactor options so --cfile-verbose is available for debugging
Unify CLI arguments behind a macro

Refactor the logging internals

Goals are:
1) make the underlying value opaque so it can be changed in the future
   if someone ever wants that.
2) explicitly separate logging between the two libraries.
3) Cleanup brain dead macros from the past.
Drop fallback implementation of STRNLEN; get a modern libc if you lack it
Mark the source as being aligned to c99 standards
Cleanup warnings flagged by clang

Drop commented out code.

Modern VCS means branches (and history) allow revision,
so no need to leave things commented out temporarily since
I didn't have access to branches in the old days...

Drop functionality for finding primes (was used by hashing)

See 2ea401713ce487a4fe22673124596f532eb423cf for the last ueser of this.

Further cleanup of inline definitions for c99.

I'm effectively lifting option #3 from this:
http://www.greenend.org.uk/rjk/tech/inline.html
Use the correct typing for unsignedBitsNeeded
Cleanup everything flagged by gcc 10.3 and -Werror
Update inline definitions for modern/fixed compilers for tar.*
Update automake/autoconf to modern standards, fix COPYING complaint, remove NEWS (see git if you want NEWS)
modernize/cleanup: take the code through code/formatting
